JDBC CONTACTS EXAMPLE

A user can view a list of contacts
	1. Create a contacts table migration and seeder file;
	2. Run migration and seeder

	        -DAO Directory
	        -JDC Directory
	        -Models Directory
	        -Database Directory
	        -Controller Directory
	Create an SQL FILE, inside Database Directory,
	- USE DB
	- CREATE TABLE
	- CREATE A FILE (insert the info)

	3. Create a Contact java bean
	CREATE A CLASS INSIDE OF THE MODLES DIRECTORY, IMPLEMENTS SERIALIZABLE
	(NAME CONTACT.JAVA)
	        - PRIVATE STRING NAME
	        - PRIVATE STRING PHONENUMBER
	        - PRIVATE LONG ID
	        - GETTERS, SETTER AND CONSTRUCTOR

    4. Create a contacts/index.jsp - view for listing out contacts


	5. Create a ContactIndexServlet - return a view to display all contacts (hard code list of contacts for now)
	CREATE A SERVLET INSIDE OF THE CONTROLLER DIRECTORY
	CREATE A JSP

	6. Create a Contacts interface to require an “all” method
	7. Implement the Contacts interface in the ListContactsDao

        Create an interface names contact
        - CRATE AN ARRAY 'LIST<CONTACT>ALL'
    INSIDE DAO CREATE A CLASS 'LIST CONTACT DAO'

	8. Refactor DaoFactory to return a Contacts DAO and use in ContactIndexServlet
	9. Implement the Contacts interface in the MySQLContactsDao
   10. Refactor the DaoFactory to use the MySQLContactsDAO


   STEP ONE COMPLETED
   STEP TWO COMPLETED

    CREATE USER 'new_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';


   STEP ONE COMPLETED
   STEP TWO COMPLETED
